
MarkdownExtended(3)        markdown_extended Manual        MarkdownExtended(3)



NNAAMMEE
       MMaarrkkddoowwnn EExxtteennddeedd


       A complete PHP 5.3 package of Markdown syntax parser (extended version)
       - Command line interface


SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       mmaarrkkddoowwnn__eexxtteennddeedd [[ooppttiioonnss]] aarrgguummeennttss


       mmaarrkkddoowwnn__eexxtteennddeedd  [--hh|--vv]  [--xx|--vv|--qq|--mm]
           [--oo _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e]  [--cc _c_o_n_f_i_g_f_i_l_e]  [--ff _f_o_r_m_a_t]
           [--nn _a_,_b]  [--ee[=_b_l_o_c_k]]  [--gg[=_n_a_m_e]]
           iinnppuutt__ffiilleennaammee  [iinnppuutt__ffiilleennaammee]  [...]
           "mmaarrkkddoowwnn ssttrriinngg rreeaadd ffrroomm SSTTDDIINN"


DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       MMaarrkkddoowwnn EExxtteennddeedd converts markdown syntax text(s) source(s) in  speci-
       fied  file(s)  (or STDIN). The rendering can be the full parsed content
       or just a part of this content.  By default, result is written  through
       STDOUT in HTML format.


       To  transform  a  file content, write its path as script argument (file
       path may be relative to current working directory and must  exist).  To
       process a list of input files, just write file paths as arguments, sep-
       arated by space.


       To transform a string read  from  STDIN,  write  it  as  last  argument
       between double-quotes or EOF.


OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       The following options are supported:

       --hh , ----hheellpp
              Get a simple help information.

       --vv , ----vveerrssiioonn
              Get the current package version number.

       --xx , ----vveerrbboossee
              Increase  script's  verbosity ; some steps are explained on STD-
              OUT.

       --qq , ----qquuiieett
              Decrease script's verbosity  ;  only  result  strings,  Markdown
              Parser and PHP error messages are written on STDOUT.

       --mm , ----mmuullttii
              Treat  multi-files input ; this options is automatically enables
              if multiple file names are found as arguments.

       --oo, ----oouuttppuutt =filename
              Specify a single file name or a file name mask to  write  gener-
              ated  content  in  ;  by default, files are generated in current
              working directory.

       --cc , ----ccoonnffiigg =filename
              Define a specific configuration filename to use for the Markdown
              Parser ; configuration files must be in `INI` format.

       --ff , ----ffoorrmmaatt =type
              Define  the  output  format to use to generate final rendering ;
              formats are stored in PHP  namespace  `\MarkdownExtended\Output-
              Format` ; default is `HTML`.

       --gg , ----ggaammuuttss [=name]
              Define a single gamut or a list of gamuts to execute on Markdown
              content parsing.

       --nn , ----nnooffiilltteerr =name-a,name-b
              Define a coma separated list of filters to disable during  Mark-
              down content parsing.

       --ee , ----eexxttrraacctt [=meta]
              Define  a  content block to extract ; default extracted block is
              `metadata`.

MMEESSSSAAGGEESS
       The script output is designed to use options  '-x'  or  '--verbose'  to
       increase  script  verbosity on STDOUT and '-q' or '--quiet' to decrease
       it. The idea is quiet simple:

       - in "nnoorrmmaall" rendering (no "verbose" neither than "quiet"  mode),  the
       result  of the processed content is rendered, with the file name header
       in case of multi-files input and command line script's errors are  ren-
       dered ;

       -  in  "vveerrbboossee"  mode,  some process informations are shown, informing
       user about what is happening, helps to follow process execution and get
       some  informations  such  as  some  string  lengthes ; the command line
       script errors are rendered ;

       - in "qquuiieett" mode, nothing is written through SDTOUT except  result  of
       parsed  content(s) ; the command line script's errors are NOT rendered.


       For all of these cases, PHP errors  catched  during  Markdown  Extended
       classes   execution   are   rendered   depending  on  your  environment
       `error_reporting` setting and script execution may  exit  with  astatus
       code '90'.


EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTT
       This script requires PHP version 5.3.0 minus.


EEXXAAMMPPLLEESS
       Classic parsing of the content of the Markdown syntax file `sample.md`:
           ~$ path/to/markdown_extended sample.md

       For the same example, writing the output in file  `sample_parsed.html`,
       run:
           ~$ path/to/markdown_extended -o sample_parsed.html sample.md

       To extract meta-data from `sample.md`, run:
           ~$ path/to/markdown_extended -e sample.md

       To  build  a  man-page formated file from the Markdown source `man-sam-
       ple.md`, run:
           ~$ path/to/markdown_extended -f man -o man-sample.man man-sample.md
           // to open it with `man`:
           ~$ man ./man-sample.man

       To transform a string read from STDIN, run:
           ~$ path/to/markdown_extended -e=body "My **Markdown** string"

